description:
Characters gain EXP not only 
from Quests but also Training. 
So stop your slacking, and get 
Training from the Team menu!
name: Attempt Training.

description:
Awakening a character 
unleashes their hidden potential, 
which in turn raises their stats. 
Try collecting Awakening Medals 
and tap into their hidden power!
name: Attempt Awakening.

description:
Maxing out a character's Lv. and 
collecting all necessary 
Awakening Medals allow you to 
perform a Z-Awakening, raising 
their max level and powering up 
their Type. 
Try it, you'll see!
name: Attempt Z-Awakening.

description:
You'll need Zeni to Train or 
Awaken characters. You can find 
it on the Quest map or after 
defeating enemies. 
Try clearing your favorite stage 
with 5000 Zeni or more in 
your pocket!
name:
Complete with a minimum of 
5000 Zeni.

description:
I bet you didn't know those blue 
Hoi-Poi Capsules on the Quest 
map contain Support Items, did 
you? 
Let's see if you can find 50 of 
them!
name: Acquire 50 Support Items.

description:
Those red Hoi-Poi Capsules on the 
Quest map contain Training 
Items. 
Go get yourself 50 of them!
name: Acquire 50 Training Items.

description:
You know, those purple 
Hoi-Poi Capsules contain 
Awakening Medals. 
Bag yourself 50 of the things!
name: Acquire 50 Awakening Medals.

description:
You can sell characters in 
exchange for Zeni, and free up 
some Character Slots at the 
same time. 
Try selling a character from the 
Team menu.
name: Sell a Character.

description:
Using a Training Item when 
Training earns the character 
more EXP. 
Try using a Training Item if 
you're having trouble leveling up 
a character!
name: Use a Training Item.

description:
Training at any location other 
than Wasteland earns characters 
more EXP, and the more 
training partners you use, the 
greater the location's effect!
name: Use a Training Location.

description:
The simplest way to treat low HP 
is to drink a Recovery Drink! 
Use a Recovery Drink during a 
Quest and you'll return here. 
Just make sure to finish the 
Quest!
name: Use a Recovery Drink.

description:
Use a Super Recovery Drink to 
restore 6000 HP. 
Well, it's better than losing! 
Use a Super Recovery Drink in 
a Quest and you'll return here. 
Just make sure to finish the 
Quest!
name: Use a Super Recovery Drink.

description:
Use the Hercule Support Item 
and gain +1 on your Ki meter. 
Use one to take you over the top 
with a Super Attack during a 
Quest. 
Make sure you finish the Quest!
name: Use Hercule.

description:
Use the Cargo Support Item will 
restore 25% of HP, whatever 
level character you use it on! 
Try using it during a Quest. 
Make sure you finish the Quest!
name: Use Cargo.

description:
Use the Oolong or Puar Support 
Items to change the color of Ki 
Spheres. 
Let's see how good you are at 
using them during a Quest! 
Make sure you finish the Quest!
name: Use a Ki Sphere color-changing item.

description:
Use the World Tournament 
Announcer Support Item to 
increase the ATK of certain 
Types for 1 turn. 
That's some ringside support! 
Try it out on a Quest and make 
sure you finish it!
name:
Use the World 
Tournament Announcer.

description:
Use the Videl Support Item and 
increase the DEF of certain 
Types for 1 turn, and maybe 
even reduce damage taken in 
some cases. 
Try it out on a Quest and make 
sure you finish it!
name: Use Videl.

description:
Use the Ranfan Support Item to 
reduce all enemies' ATK. 
She sure is distractingly 
beautiful! 
Try it out on a Quest and make 
sure you finish it!
name: Use Ranfan.

description:
Consistency is the key to 
success, but for now, try logging 
in tomorrow and we'll take it 
from there.
name: Log in for 2 straight days.

description:
There are 2 kinds of login bonus. 
Chain Login Bonuses are 
rewarded for consecutive daily 
logins. 
I'm sure you'll have no problem 
logging in 3 days in a row!
name: Log in for 3 straight days.

description:
Mission Rewards are instantly 
yours to use, but Login Bonuses 
get sent to your gift box. 
Don't forget to go collect them! 
I'll give you a Dragon Stone for 
logging in daily for 7 straight 
days!
name: Log in for 7 straight days.

description:
You never know when you'll 
need a Device Transfer Code. 
I bet it'll come in handy if you 
need to contact customer 
support! 
Create one by selecting 
"Device Transfer" from the 
MENU.
name: Create a Device Transfer Code.

description:
Find all the Dragon Balls lying 
around the Quest map yet? 
Just tap a greyed-out one on 
the Shenron screen to learn 
its location. 
Let's see if you can find 3 to start 
with!
name: Collect 3 Dragon Balls.

description:
You can't do anything with the 
Dragon Balls until you have all 7, 
but I'm sure you'll have no 
problem finding them all!
name: Collect 7 Dragon Balls.

description:
With all 7 Dragon Balls in your 
possession, you can have a wish 
granted. 
Summon Shenron from The 
Shenron screen.
name: Have Shenron grant 1 wish.

description:
Awakening Medal stages feature 
enemies of a single Type. 
A team of one Type could be a 
powerful counter to such 
opponents. 
Try clearing a stage using a 
team made of only one Type. 
Make sure to finish the stage, 
though!
name: Use a team of all the same Type.

description:
1 STA Point is restored every 5 
minutes. 
You can see how much time is 
left before the next point is 
recovered at the top of the 
screen. 
How about this—I'll give you a 
reward for using 100 STA Points!
name: Use 100 STA Points.

description:
Clearing a QUEST earns you 
Player EXP, and your Rank can 
go up. 
A new Rank increases your 
maximum STA Points and Team 
Cost limit. 
Let's see if you can get to Rank 
10!
name: Reach Rank 10.

description:
Here's a useful tip to help you
progress: try clearing the limited 
daily stage
“Training in the Clouds” once.
name: Clear “Training in the Clouds” once.

description:
Here's a useful tip to help you
progress: try clearing the limited 
daily stage
“Training in the Clouds”3 times.
name: Clear “Training in the Clouds” 3 times.

description:
Here's a useful tip to help you 
progress: try clearing the limited
daily stage
“Training in the Clouds”5 times.
name: Clear “Training in the Clouds” 5 times.

description:
Here's a useful tip to help you
progress: try clearing the limited
daily stage
“Training in the Clouds”7 times.
name: Clear “Training in the Clouds” 7 times.

description:
Here's a useful tip to help you
progress: try clearing the limited
daily stage
“Training in the Clouds”10 times.
name: Clear “Training in the Clouds” 10 times.

description:
Here's a useful tip to help you
progress: try clearing the limited
daily stage
“Training in the Clouds”15 times.
name: Clear “Training in the Clouds” 15 times.

description:
Clear stage 1 of the Strike Event
“An Epic Showdown”
on NORMAL once.
name:
Clear Stage 1 of “An Epic Showdown” 
on NORMAL.

description:
Clear stage 2 of the Strike Event
“An Epic Showdown”
on NORMAL once.
name:
Clear Stage 2 of “An Epic Showdown” 
on NORMAL.

description:
Looks like Baba's Shop 
has opened. 
You can trade any items you 
don’t need for Trade Points.
You can access Baba's Shop 
From 'Shop.'
name: Get Trade Points.

description:
Try buying something 
at Baba's Shop 
using Trade Points. 
If you can't find anything 
you want now, 
you can wait until 
new products come in!
name: Use Trade Points.

description:
The more the choices 
at Baba's Shop, the better! 
You can use your Trade Points 
to expand the product range.
name:
Expand the product range of 
Baba's Shop.

description:
The more choices you have 
at Baba's Shop, the higher 
the chance of you finding 
an item you want. 
Unlock three Trade Slots.
name:
Further expand the product Range 
of Baba's Shop.

description:
At the Zeni Shop you can 
use Zeni instead of 
Trade Points to purchase items.
If you have some spare Zeni, 
why not go shopping?
name: Use Zeni at Baba's Shop.

description:
Linking to a Facebook account 
makes it easy to transfer game 
data to a new device quickly. 
Your data will also be kept safe, 
just in case something happens 
to your current device. 
Select "Device Transfer/Back 
Up" from the menu.
name:
Link Dokkan Battle to 
your Facebook account.

description:
Clear the "Turtle School 
Training!" event 1 time!

Complete it and claim the 
rewards by 15:59:59 PST
of each day.
name:
[Daily] Clear 
"Turtle School Training" once!

description:
Pick any stage you like and 
clear it three times! 

Complete it and claim the 
rewards by 15:59:59 PST
of each day.
name:
[Daily] 
Clear a stage 3 times!

description:
Go to "Friend Summon" and 
perform 1 Summon! 
 
Complete it and claim the 
rewards by 15:59:59 PST
of each day.
name:
[Daily] Perform 1 
Summon on Friend Summon.

description:
Give any of your characters 
a Training!  

Complete it and claim the 
rewards by 15:59:59 PST
of each day.
name: [Daily] Get stronger by Training

description:
Purchase goods at Baba's Shop 
with Trade Pts!  Please note that 
purchasing “0 Trade Pt" items 
and unlocking a Trade Slot will 
not complete the mission.  

Complete it and claim the 
rewards by 15:59:59 PST
of each day.
name:
[Daily] Purchase goods at 
Baba's Shop with Trade Pts!

description:
冒険やイベントで
ACTを一日合計50以上
消費してみましょう!
※天下一武道会で
消費されたACTは
含まれません。

条件達成と報酬受取は
各日の23:59:59まで
となります。
name:
[Daily] Consume at least 
50 STA (weekend only)!

description:
The EXP a character gains from 
a Training Partner depends on 
the character's level. 
Try using a Training Partner 
With their level maxed out!
name:
Use a Max-Lv. character as 
a Training Partner.

description:
When training a character, use 
an identical character as a 
Training Partner to raise their 
Super Attack Lv. 
The higher a Super Attack's Lv., 
the more powerful it is! 
Try raising a character's Super 
Attack Lv.
name: Level up a Super Attack.

description:
Perform a Z-Awakening to raise 
a character's Rarity as well as 
powering up his/her Type. 
His/her Max-Lv. will increase. 
Let's try Z-Awakening an AGL 
Type character.
name: Z-Awaken an AGL-Type character.

description:
Perform a Z-Awakening to raise 
a character's Rarity as well as 
powering up his/her Type. 
His/her Max-Lv. will increase. 
Let's try Z-Awakening a STR 
Type character.
name: Z-Awaken a STR-Type character.

description:
Perform a Z-Awakening to raise 
a character's Rarity as well as 
powering up his/her Type. 
His/her Max-Lv. will increase. 
Let's try Z-Awakening a PHY 
Type character.
name: Z-Awaken a PHY-Type character.

description:
Perform a Z-Awakening to raise 
a character's Rarity as well as 
powering up his/her Type. 
His/her Max-Lv. will increase. 
Let's try Z-Awakening an INT 
Type character.
name: Z-Awaken an INT-Type character.

description:
Perform a Z-Awakening to raise 
a character's Rarity as well as 
powering up his/her Type. 
His/her Max-Lv. will increase. 
Let's try Z-Awakening a TEQ 
Type character.
name: Z-Awaken a TEQ-Type character.

description:
High-rank Types powered up by 
Z-Awakening outperform 
standard Types. 
An attack that typically inflicts 
great damage against a 
standard Type enemy, will do 
less damage against a high-rank 
Type enemy. 
Turn 5 characters into Super 
Types.
name: Create 5 Super Type characters.

description:
Super and Extreme Types are 
high-rank Types that work in 
opposition to each other. E.g. 
an S. AGL attack against an 
E. STR will inflict more damage 
than an S. AGL attack against an 
S. STR. 
Turn 5 characters into Extreme 
Types.
name: Create 5 Extreme Type characters.

description:
Let's see you clear any stage 
you like after acquiring 50000 
Zeni or more. 
Look out for those Zeni tiles, and 
I'm sure with a few victories 
under your belt You'll be flush 
with cash!
name:
Clear a stage with 
50000 Zeni acquired.

description:
Korin probably told you already, 
but the blue Hoi-Poi Capsules give 
you Support Items. 
Try clearing a stage after 
acquiring 5 or more of them 
along the way!
name:
Clear a stage with 5 or more 
Support Items acquired.

description:
Korin probably covered this part 
already, but the red 
Hoi-Poi Capsules give you Training 
Items. 
Try clearing a stage after 
acquiring 5 or more of them 
along the way!
name:
Clear a stage with 5 or more 
Training Items acquired.

description:
Korin probably explained this 
already, but the purple 
Hoi-Poi Capsules give you 
Awakening Medals. 
Try clearing a stage after 
acquiring 5 or more of them 
along the way!
name:
Clear a stage with 5 or more 
Awakening Medals acquired.

description:
A problem shared is a problem 
halved! The more friends you 
have to depend on, the easier it 
is to get through those troubling 
times. 
Let's see you make pals with 25 
people or more!
name: Make 25 Friends.

description:
Use the King Support Item to 
raise all allies' Ki by 1 for 3 turns. 
Great for those drawn-out boss 
fights. 
Use one in a Quest, and make 
sure you finish it!
name: Use King.

description:
Use the Launch (Normal) 
Support Item and raise the 
attacking ally's Ki by a random 
amount. 
Sometimes you just gotta try 
your luck! 
Use one in a Quest, and make 
sure you finish it!
name: Use Launch (Normal).

description:
Use the Bulma Support Item and 
you can raise all allies' ATK and 
DEF by 20% for 3 turns. 
A balanced approach is 
sometimes the best. 
Use one in a Quest, and make 
sure you finish it!
name: Use Bulma.

description:
Focusing your team lineup on 
the ATK stat is the name of this 
test. 
Form a team with a combined 
ATK of 20000 or more then clear 
a stage and come see me!
name:
Form a team with a combined 
ATK of 20000 or higher.

description:
High HP increases the odds of 
outlasting your enemy. 
Form a team with a combined 
HP of 25000 or more then clear 
a stage and come see me!
name:
Form a team with a combined 
HP of 25000 or higher.

description:
The Link Skill "Z Fighters" 
increases your ATK by 15%. 
And the more allies who possess 
the skill, the greater the chance 
to unleash it. 
Form a team made only of 
characters with the "Z Fighters" 
skill, then clear a stage!
name:
Bolster a team with 
the Link Skill "Z Fighters."

description:
You don't need me to tell you 
this, but Login Bonuses only go 
to those who log in! 
Let's see if you can log in for a 
total of 15 days. 
You'll get a Dragon Stone if you 
do!
name: Log in for 15 days total.

description:
The Login Bonus for the 30th 
day is two varieties of valuable 
Awakening Medals. 
Make it that far and you'll also 
get 5 Dragon Stones from yours 
truly!
name: Log in for 30 days total.

description:
I wonder if you can defeat 100 
Saibaimen. 
You'll often find them in stages 
related to Saiyans. 100 should 
be a piece of cake for someone 
like you, but if you quit half way 
it won't count!
name: Defeat 100 Saibaimen.

description:
How's the search for the Dragon 
Balls going? 
You'll need to have a wish 
granted before they'll reappear in 
the next area. 
Let's see if you can have 4 
wishes granted before you clear 
Areas up to and including Area 
9!
name: Have Shenron grant 4 wishes.

description:
How's your Quest going? 
Logging in means little if you're 
not getting stronger! 
I'll let you have access to the 
"Snake Way" Training Location 
if you use over 500 STA Points.
name: Use 500 STA Points.

description:
Is that Rank of yours getting 
higher? 
And I don't mean your 
allies' Ranks! Quest boss stages 
on HARD and Z-HARD raise 
your Player Rank faster. 
Let's see you reach Rank 20.
name: Reach Rank 20.

description:
Your Rank plays a part in which 
Friends you can take on Quests 
as guests. 
The higher your Rank, the 
tougher the Friends you can to 
take with you. 
Let's see you reach Rank 30.
name: Reach Rank 30.

description:
Are you progressing through the 
standard Quest areas, hmm? 
Don't forget to progress the 
story, collect Dragon Stone 
Quest rewards and, of course, 
the Dragon Balls themselves! 
Try clearing all stages on 
NORMAL up to and including 
Area 9.
name:
Clear all stages on 
NORMAL up till Area 9.

description:
There are some paths that can 
only be traversed on HARD 
mode, with more Zeni and EXP 
up for grabs. 
Try clearing all stages on HARD 
up to and Including Area 9.
name:
Clear all stages on 
HARD up till Area 9.

description:
A test is in order! 
Clear the 1st area
—"A Gloomy Parallel World"—
without using Support Items or a 
Continue on any one of the
stages in this area.
name:
Clear a stage without using 
an item on NORMAL (1).

description:
A test is in order! 
Clear the 2nd area
—"The Ultimate Life Form!"—
without using Support Items or a 
Continue on any one of the
stages in this area.
name:
Clear a stage without using 
an item on NORMAL (2).

description:
A test is in order! 
Clear the 3rd area
—"A Call to Arms"—
without using Support Items or a 
Continue on any one of the
stages in this area.
name:
Clear a stage without using 
an item on NORMAL (3).

description:
A test is in order! 
Clear the 4th area
—"The Emperor's Wrath"—
without using Support Items or a 
Continue on any one of the
stages in this area.
name:
Clear a stage without using 
an item on NORMAL (4).

description:
A test is in order! 
Clear the 5th area
—"The Dreaded Ginyu Force"—
without using Support Items or a 
Continue on any one of the
stages in this area.
name:
Clear a stage without using 
an item on NORMAL (5).

description:
A test is in order! 
Clear the 6th area
—"The Androids Attack!"—
without using Support Items or a 
Continue on any one of the
stages in this area.
name:
Clear a stage without using 
an item on NORMAL (6).

description:
A test is in order! 
Clear the 7th area
—"Assault of the Saiyans!"—
without using Support Items or a
Continue on any one of the
stages in this area.
name:
Clear a stage without using 
an item on NORMAL (7).

description:
A test is in order! 
Clear the 8th area
—"Merciless Frieza"—
without using Support Items or a 
Continue on any one of the
stages in this area.
name:
Clear a stage without using 
an item on NORMAL (8).

description:
A test is in order! 
Clear the 9th area
—"Arise, Saiyan Prince"—
without using Support Items or a 
Continue on any one of the
stages in this area.
name:
Clear a stage without using 
an item on NORMAL (9).

description:
Are you progressing through 
standard Quest areas, hmm? 
Don't forget to progress the 
story, collect Dragon Stone 
Quest rewards and, of course, 
the Dragon Balls themselves! 
Try clearing all stages on 
NORMAL from Areas 10 to 12.
name:
Clear all stages on NORMAL 
from Areas 10 to 12.

description:
There are some paths that can 
only be traversed on HARD 
mode, with more Zeni and EXP 
up for grabs. 
Try clearing all stages on HARD 
From Areas 10 to 12.
name:
Clear all stages on HARD 
from Areas 10 to 12.

description:
A test is in order! 
Clear the 10th area
—"Red Ribbon Machinations"—
without using Support Items or a 
Continue on any one of the
stages in this area.
name:
Clear a stage without using 
an item on NORMAL (10).

description:
A test is in order! 
Clear the 11th area
—"Unknown Saiyans"—
without using Support Items or a 
Continue on any one of the
stages in this area.
name:
Clear a stage without using 
an item on NORMAL (11).

description:
A test is in order!

description:

of your choice with 150000 Zeni 
or more acquired.
You might struggle to collect that
amount of Zeni and finish one of
those tougher stages, so how 
about giving "Big Bucks Hercule 
Challenge" a go?

Clear a stage with 
150000 Zeni acquired.

description:
Clear a stage with 10 or more 
Support Items acquired. 
It shouldn't be too difficult if you 
choose a stage where 
the enemies drop Support Items.

Clear a stage with 10 
or more Support Items acquired.

description:
Clear a stage with 10 or more 
Training Items acquired. 
Your best chance of success is 
to attempt the challenge at 
an event focused on Training.
name:
Clear a stage with 10 
or more Training Items acquired.

description:
Clear a stage with 10 or more 
Awakening Medals acquired. 
Your best chance to achieve 
this is to attempt Daily Events 
with a high difficulty level.
name:
Clear a stage with 10 
or more Awakening Medals acquired.

description:
Use the Dende Support Item to 
restore all HP and heal all allies'
status ailments. 
This item might just turn the tide 
of battle! Use one in a Quest, 
And make sure you finish it!
name: Use Dende.

description:
Use the Baba Support Item and 
you'll be able to foresee an 
enemy's attack and nullify their 
Super Attack for 1 turn. 
Use one in a Quest, and make 
sure you finish it!
name: Use Baba.

description:
Use the Ghost Usher Support 
Item to delay the enemy's turn 
for 1 round. 
Perfect for when you're 
desperate to avoid getting 
attacked! 
Use one in a Quest, and make 
sure you finish it!
name: Use Ghost Usher.

description:
Use the King Yemma Support 
Item to halve damage taken for 
1 turn. 
Great for when all allies have a 
chance to be hit. 
Use one in a Quest, and make 
sure you finish it!
name: Use King Yemma.

description:
Are your characters getting 
tougher? 
You'll need powerful attacks 
when facing powerful enemies. 
Form a team with a combined 
ATK of 25000 or more, then 
clear a stage and come see me!
name:
Form a team with a combined 
ATK of 25000 or higher.

description:
Try as you like, not even allies 
that are strong against an 
enemy's Type can guard an 
attack well enough to reduce its 
damage to 0. 
The more HP, the better, I say. 
Form a team with a combined 
HP of 35000 or more, then clear 
a stage and come see me!
name:
Form a team with a combined 
HP of 35000 or higher.

description:
Not only Training but also 
logging in daily is essential to 
your continued success. 
Log in for 60 days total and I will 
give you 5 Dragon Stones. 
Or maybe you'd prefer a joke, 
hmm?
name: Log in for 60 days total.

description:
You're efforts haven't gone 
unnoticed. 
Let's make it interesting! 
I'll give you 5 Dragon Stones if 
you can make it to 90 days of 
logins.
name: Log in for 90 days total.

description:
I, too, am prone to forgetfulness! 
It's such an easy thing to 
do—skipping a day of logging in. 
But if you can log in 30 days in a 
row, I'll give you 
[Innocent Challenger] Goku (Kid)
[SR]. He's Lv. 59!
name: Log in daily for 30 straight days.

description:
Hey there! How's the old
Rank looking? Have you
been raising it like you 
should? When you feel the
need to increase your max 
STA, you're best off
playing at a harder difficulty!

Try to reach Rank 50!
name: Reach Rank 50.

description:
Is your Team Cost high 
enough? If you want to beat
stronger enemies, you'll 
need to increase your
maximum Team Cost by 
raising your Rank.

Try to reach Rank 60!
name: Reach Rank 60.

description:
Do you need some help from 
stronger allies? Well, as your 
Rank increases, the Guests 
you can choose from will be 
of higher Rank as well!

Try to reach Rank 70!
name: Reach Rank 70.

description:
Have you tried to level up your 
Rank on Quests? If there are 
any stages you've not cleared 
yet, you should try them out! 
It'll be a great way to raise
your Rank and earn 
Dragon Stones in the process!

Try to reach Rank 80!
name: Reach Rank 80.

description:
Ever noticed announcements 
in the News section for 
Events that grant
bonus Rank EXP? 
Try them out the next time 
you need a little EXP boost!
name: Reach Rank 90.

description:
Did you know the Event 
"Pan's Secret Adventure"?
If you want to raise 
your Rank in record time, 
this Event is definitely worth 
a look!

Try to reach Rank 100!
name: Reach Rank 100.

description:
You might have reached 
Rank 100, but there's no
time to rest on your laurels! 
You've come this far, but the 
sky's the limit for you, 
I'm sure!

Try to reach Rank 110!
name: Reach Rank 110.

description:
Now you're capable of 
handling more Events than
ever before, don't you get 
the feeling you might be
lacking a little STA? 
Remember that raising your
Rank will increase your 
max STA.

Try to reach Rank 120!
name: Reach Rank 120.

description:
Howdy! Have you recruited 
some powerful allies yet? 
Let me tell you, it doesn't 
matter how many strong 
characters you have, they'll 
go to waste if you can't 
include them in your team!

Try to reach Rank 130 and 
raise your maximum Team Cost!
name: Reach Rank 130.

description:
If you run up against an 
enemy you just can't beat, 
it might be time to call in a 
friend for back-up.

As your Rank gets higher, 
the chance of a strong Guest 
showing up also increases!

Try to reach Rank 140!
name: Reach Rank 140.

description:
You can earn Dragon Stones 
from Events as well as Quests. 
If there are any Events you've 
not tried yet, you should give 
them a go! It'll be a great
way to raise your Rank and 
earn Dragon Stones in
the process!

Try to reach Rank 150!
name: Reach Rank 150.

description:
You've finally reached Rank 
150! It's a remarkable thing 
to see you come this far. 
But I can tell there's a lot more 
to come from you yet!

Try to reach Rank 160!
name: Reach Rank 160.

description:
Do you always check the 
News announcements every
day? Make sure you don't 
miss out on any Events that 
grant extra Rank EXP. They're 
an excellent way to raise your 
Rank even higher!

Try to reach Rank 170!
name: Reach Rank 170.

description:
You've been testing yourself 
on Quests for a little while now, 
so maybe you know this already,
but the further you progress 
through the Quests, the more 
Rank EXP you'll earn. 
Bear this in mind if you ever 
need to raise your Rank quickly.

Try to reach Rank 180!
name: Reach Rank 180.

description:
Are you finding it harder and 
harder to raise your Rank? 
If so, try out the Event 
"Pan's Secret Adventure"! 
You'll be rewarded with 
a ton of Rank EXP for 
clearing it!

Try to reach Rank 190!
name: Reach Rank 190.

description:
You're getting close to Rank 
200 now! You've come so far 
and achieved so much. 
It won't be long until you've 
surpassed the next big 
milestone!

Try to reach Rank 200!
name: Reach Rank 200.

On HARD, enemies are stronger
and there are more of them, too.

Let your guard down 
and you'll take a beating!

See if you can clear 
Areas 25 to 27 on HARD.

Clear all stages on HARD 
from Areas 25 to 27.

description:
When it comes to Z-HARD, 
you better be ready.

It's high risk, high reward,
as the Dragon Stones and 
EXP you earn are 
that much greater!

Try clearing all stages on 
Z-HARD from Areas 25 to 27.

Clear all stages on Z-HARD 
from Areas 25 to 27.

The path ahead is reserved for
seasoned experts alone! Prepare 
for the worst should you go...

But if you think you can 
complete Areas 25 to 27 on 
SUPER difficulty, then 
go ahead and give it a shot!

Clear all stages on SUPER 
from Areas 25 to 27.

those Dragon Balls?
You won't find them in the 
next location unless you have 
a wish granted first.

If you can collect all 
Dragon Balls 17 times,
you'll be rewarded with 
something good!

description:
The World Tournament has
begun! Your total Tournament
Points will be awarded at the end
of the Tournament. Try getting at
least 1 point! Hahahaha!
Ends: July 14th (Tue) 12:59 PM
name: Enter the 1st World Tournament.

description:
The preliminaries take the form
of a battle royal with 4
contestants, but the finals will be
1-on-1. Can you make it to the
quarterfinals at the 1st World
Tournament?
Ends: July 14th (Tue) 12:59 PM
name: Advance to the quarterfinals.

description:
If you can win the World
Tournament even once, as a
former champion myself,
I'll recognize your skill.
You might even get my
autograph, if you're lucky!
Ends: July 14th (Tue) 12:59 PM
name: Win the World Tournament.

description:
You can win once by accident,
but it takes a true champion to
win twice!
Ends: July 14th (Tue) 12:59 PM
name: Win the World Tournament twice.

description:
I've won the World Tournament
3 times, y’know. That's not
something you'll ever achieve!
Gahahaha!
Ends: July 14th (Tue) 12:59 PM
name: Win the World Tournament 3 times.

description:
You want to win the World
Tournament 4 times and beat my
record? Hmph! Try all you like!
Ends: July 14th (Tue) 12:59 PM
name: Win the World Tournament 4 times.

description:
You want to win the World
Tournament 5 times and smash
my record? Hmph!
Try all you like!
Ends: July 14th (Tue) 12:59 PM
name: Win the World Tournament 5 times.

description:
You want to win the World
Tournament 7 times and
obliterate my record? Hmph!
Try all you like!
Ends: July 14th (Tue) 12:59 PM
name: Win the World Tournament 7 times.

description:
You want to win the World
Tournament 10 times?!
D-don't be stupid! You'd have be
a big cheat to do that!
Ends: July 14th (Tue) 12:59 PM
name: Win the World Tournament 10 times.

description:
You want to win the World
Tournament 20 times?!
D-don't be stupid! You'd have be
a big cheat to do that!
Ends: July 14th (Tue) 12:59 PM
name: Win the World Tournament 20 times.

description:
You want to win the World
Tournament 30 times?!
D-don't be stupid! You'd have be
a big cheat to do that!
Ends: July 14th (Tue) 12:59 PM
name: Win the World Tournament 30 times.

description:
Your Tournament Points will be
awarded at the end of the
tournament. For starters, try
getting at least 5000 points!
Ends: July 14th (Tue) 12:59 PM
name: Reach King Chappa Class.

description:
Your Tournament Points will be
awarded at the end of the
tournament. Just remember,
your points won't be updated
until after the tournament!
Aim for 25,000 points!
Ends: July 14th (Tue) 12:59 PM
name: Reach Hercule Class.

description:
If your total Tournament Points
hit 50,000, you'll reach Videl
Class! Huh? Wait a second.
Why is my Class so low?!
Ends: July 14th (Tue) 12:59 PM
name: Reach Videl Class.

description:
If your total Tournament Points hit
100,000, you'll reach Master
Roshi Class! Huh? Wait a second.
Why is my Class so low?!
Ends: July 14th (Tue) 12:59 PM
name: Reach Master Roshi Class.

description:
If your total Tournament Points hit
150,000, you'll reach Korin Class!
Huh? Wait a second.
Why is my Class so low?!
Ends: July 14th (Tue) 12:59 PM
name: Reach Korin Class.

description:
If your Tournament Points hit
250,000, you'll be recognized as
Kami Class. The further you get
in the tournament, the more
Tournament Points you'll get!
Ends: July 14 (Tue) 12:59 PM
name: Reach Kami Class.

description:
If your Tournament Points hit
500,000, you'll be recognized as
King Yemma Class.
The further you get in the
tournament, the more
Tournament Points you'll get!
Ends: July 14 (Tue) 12:59 PM
name: Reach King Yemma Class.

description:
If your Tournament Points hit
1,000,000, you'll be recognized
as King Kai Class. The further
you get in the tournament,
the more Tournament Points
you'll get!
Ends: July 14 (Tue) 12:59 PM
name: Reach King Kai Class.

description:
If your total Tournament Points
hit 1,500,000, you'll reach
Supreme Kai Class! You don't
have to win; just keep at it and
you'll get there eventually!
Ends: July 14 (Tue) 12:59 PM
name: Reach Supreme Kai Class.

description:
If your total Tournament Points
hit 2,500,000, you'll reach Elder
Kai Class! You don't have to win;
just keep at it and you'll get there
eventually!
Ends: July 14 (Tue) 12:59 PM
name: Reach Elder Kai Class.

description:
If your total Tournament Points
hit 5,000,000, you'll reach Beerus
Class! You don't have to win;
just keep at it and you'll get there
eventually!
Ends: July 14 (Tue) 12:59 PM
name: Reach Beerus Class.

description:
Completing Quests will grant you 
EXP that will raise your Rank. 
And as your Rank goes up, your
maximum STA and Team Cost 
will increase too!

Try to reach Rank 10!
name: Reach Rank 10.

description:
I'm sure you've been powering up 
your characters, but make sure 
you don't neglect your own Rank!
Compared to NORMAL, stages 
on HARD and Z-HARD grant 
more EXP and make it easier 
to raise that Rank!

Try to reach Rank 20!
name: Reach Rank 20.

description:
Your Rank helps determine 
which Guests you can take 
along with you. 
The higher your Rank, 
the stronger the players you 
can access!

Try to reach Rank 30!
name: Reach Rank 30.

description:
I recommend taking on
Quests to raise your Rank.

Summon powerful characters
with Dragon Stones obtained
by clearing stages to
accompany you on your way
to greater heights!

Try to reach Rank 40!
name: Reach Rank 40.

description:
Hey there! How's the old
Rank looking? Have you
been raising it like you 
should? When you feel the
need to increase your max 
STA, you're best off
playing at a harder difficulty!

Try to reach Rank 50!
name: Reach Rank 50.

description:
Is your Team Cost high 
enough? If you want to beat
stronger enemies, you'll 
need to increase your
maximum Team Cost by 
raising your Rank.

Try to reach Rank 60!
name: Reach Rank 60.

description:
Do you need some help from 
stronger allies? Well, as your 
Rank increases, the Guests 
you can choose from will be 
of higher Rank as well!

Try to reach Rank 70!
name: Reach Rank 70.

description:
Have you tried to level up your 
Rank on Quests? If there are 
any stages you've not cleared 
yet, you should try them out! 
It'll be a great way to raise
your Rank and earn 
Dragon Stones in the process!

Try to reach Rank 80!
name: Reach Rank 80.

description:
Ever noticed announcements 
in the News section for 
Events that grant
bonus Rank EXP? 
Try them out the next time 
you need a little EXP boost!
name: Reach Rank 90.

description:
Did you know the Event 
"Pan's Secret Adventure"?
If you want to raise 
your Rank in record time, 
this Event is definitely worth 
a look!

Try to reach Rank 100!
name: Reach Rank 100.

description:
You might have reached 
Rank 100, but there's no
time to rest on your laurels! 
You've come this far, but the 
sky's the limit for you, 
I'm sure!

Try to reach Rank 110!
name: Reach Rank 110.

description:
Now you're capable of 
handling more Events than
ever before, don't you get 
the feeling you might be
lacking a little STA? 
Remember that raising your
Rank will increase your 
max STA.

Try to reach Rank 120!
name: Reach Rank 120.

description:
Howdy! Have you recruited 
some powerful allies yet? 
Let me tell you, it doesn't 
matter how many strong 
characters you have, they'll 
go to waste if you can't 
include them in your team!

Try to reach Rank 130 and 
raise your maximum Team Cost!
name: Reach Rank 130.

description:
If you run up against an 
enemy you just can't beat, 
it might be time to call in a 
friend for back-up.

As your Rank gets higher, 
the chance of a strong Guest 
showing up also increases!

Try to reach Rank 140!
name: Reach Rank 140.

description:
You can earn Dragon Stones 
from Events as well as Quests. 
If there are any Events you've 
not tried yet, you should give 
them a go! It'll be a great
way to raise your Rank and 
earn Dragon Stones in
the process!

Try to reach Rank 150!
name: Reach Rank 150.

description:
You've finally reached Rank 
150! It's a remarkable thing 
to see you come this far. 
But I can tell there's a lot more 
to come from you yet!

Try to reach Rank 160!
name: Reach Rank 160.

description:
Do you always check the 
News announcements every
day? Make sure you don't 
miss out on any Events that 
grant extra Rank EXP. They're 
an excellent way to raise your 
Rank even higher!

Try to reach Rank 170!
name: Reach Rank 170.

description:
You've been testing yourself 
on Quests for a little while now, 
so maybe you know this already,
but the further you progress 
through the Quests, the more 
Rank EXP you'll earn. 
Bear this in mind if you ever 
need to raise your Rank quickly.

Try to reach Rank 180!
name: Reach Rank 180.

description:
Are you finding it harder and 
harder to raise your Rank? 
If so, try out the Event 
"Pan's Secret Adventure"! 
You'll be rewarded with 
a ton of Rank EXP for 
clearing it!

Try to reach Rank 190!
name: Reach Rank 190.

description:
You're getting close to Rank 
200 now! You've come so far 
and achieved so much. 
It won't be long until you've 
surpassed the next big 
milestone!

Try to reach Rank 200!
name: Reach Rank 200.

description:
So it seems like you've 
reached Rank 200.
By now you should have 
gained some confidence 
in your strength.
However, there's still room 
for you to improve.

Try to reach Rank 220!
name: Reach Rank 220.

description:
Have you had a go 
at "Ultimate Clash"?
If not, you may as well 
set it as one of your goals 
and give it a shot.

But keep the objective of 
this mission in mind as well.
Try to reach Rank 240!
name: Reach Rank 240.

description:
Are you challenging 
"Pan's Secret Adventure" 
every week?
You can only challenge 
this event once per week.

Remember to gain lots of 
Rank EXP every week and 
aim for Rank 260!
name: Reach Rank 260.

description:
Take on the Prime Battle events 
available from Fridays to 
Sundays if you haven't 
met any LR allies yet.
Increase Team Cost by 
raising your Rank to add 
strong but high Cost 
characters to your team!

Try to reach Rank 280!
name: Reach Rank 280.

description:
Almost Rank 300!

Don't slack off just yet! 
Keep challenging Quests 
and Events. You will reach
greater heights eventually!

Try to reach Rank 300!
name: Reach Rank 300.

description:
Get "Supreme Kai Stones"
to exchange for items
by completing certain
Quest conditions.

Raise your Rank and complete
these conditions if you can!

Try to reach Rank 320!
name: Reach Rank 320.

description:
Raising Rank should be 
more difficult now.

Get the much needed 
Rank EXP in the 
once-a-week
"Pan's Secret Adventure"!

Try to reach Rank 340!
name: Reach Rank 340.

description:
You can probably clear
"Ultimate Clash" now, right?
Collecting "Battlefield Memories"
in "Ultimate Clash" and
using them to exchange
for characters that can be
Dokkan Awakened to LR can 
be a new goal of yours!

Try to reach Rank 360!
name: Reach Rank 360.

description:
Check the announcements 
if you find it hard to 
raise your Rank.

Aim for events that give 
lots of Rank EXP. 
They are the shortcuts to 
faster growth!

Try to reach Rank 380!
name: Reach Rank 380.

description:
Finally reached Rank 380!
This isn't an easy task.
I've been hearing about 
your great efforts.

I hope you'll keep 
moving forward like this!

Try to reach Rank 400!
name: Reach Rank 400.

description:
Rank 400 reached!

But this doesn't end here!
Aim for more achievements
and show how much 
you've grown!

Try to reach Rank 420!
name: Reach Rank 420.

description:
It seems like your Rank 
has reached 420. 
You should be able to do 
more things and face 
stronger enemies 
from now on!

Don't skip your training!
Try to reach Rank 440!
name: Reach Rank 440.

description:
It seems like 
you're making some
good progress over there.
Keep up the good work 
and you'll definitely 
achieve your goal.

Try to reach Rank 460!
name: Reach Rank 460.

description:
Looks like you have been
gaining experience steadily.

Persistence is important!

Try to reach Rank 480!
name: Reach Rank 480.

description:
You're finally here.
Rank 500 is not far away
anymore.

It's a pleasure to see
all the hard work you've put in.

Try to reach Rank 500!
name: Reach Rank 500.

description:
It's high time you completed a 
Quest! Best if you start on an 
easier difficulty, raise your Rank
nice and steadily, then you'll be 
ready for any new Quests that 
come along!

Try to reach Rank 5!
name: Reach Rank 5.

description:
Completing Quests will grant you 
EXP that will raise your Rank. 
And as your Rank goes up, your
maximum STA and Team Cost 
will increase too!

Try to reach Rank 10!
name: Reach Rank 10.

description:
Did you know that you can get 
Dragon Stones for completing 
Quests? Better get out there and
challenge yourself on some 
stages!

Try to reach Rank 15!
name: Reach Rank 15.

description:
I'm sure you've been powering up 
your characters, but make sure 
you don't neglect your own Rank!
Compared to NORMAL, stages 
on HARD and Z-HARD grant 
more EXP and make it easier 
to raise that Rank!

Try to reach Rank 20!
name: Reach Rank 20.

description:
Are you feeling restricted by your 
max Team Cost? Well if you want 
to put some powerful new
characters in your team, you'll 
need to raise your Rank first!

Try to reach Rank 25!
name: Reach Rank 25.

description:
Your Rank helps determine 
which Guests you can take 
along with you. 
The higher your Rank, 
the stronger the players you 
can access!

Try to reach Rank 30!
name: Reach Rank 30.

description:
Did you know you can collect 
Support Items during Quests? 
Take part in plenty of Events and 
collect as many different kinds of 
Support Items as you can!

Try to reach Rank 35!
name: Reach Rank 35.

description:
Have you heard of the Event 
"Pan's Secret Adventure"? 
If you want to raise your 
Rank in record time, 
then this Event is for you!

Try to reach Rank 40!
name: Reach Rank 40.

description:
Do you feel like the enemies are 
getting tougher? Well they are! 
As you progress through the 
Quests, the enemies will get 
stronger and stronger! 
Raise your Rank and try 
to include characters of higher
rarity in your team!

Try to reach Rank 45!
name: Reach Rank 45.
